Table A: Running EQ6 from EQ3/6-V8.0a (R43a) for PC
Description= 'Evaporate sea water; PHRQPITZ test problem 6'
This is part of the EQ3/6 Test Case Library
Evaporate sea water by treating H2O as a reactant with a negative relative
dissolution rate. The log pCO2 is fixed at the atmospheric value of -3.5 by
means of an nffg option. Only dolomite; gypsum; and halite are allowed to
precipitate. This is done by means of the nxopt subset-selection option
'all'; which suppresses all minerals; and by the nxopex option; which
permits exceptions (here dolomite; gypsum; and halite) to be specified.
Purpose: to compare against results obtained from PHRQPITZ (Plummer et
